1174: **Plan rationale (do NOT include in `enable-msw.ts`):** The existing `jest.setup.js` declares `global.fetch = jest.fn()` before any test file loads. A bare `import 'whatwg-fetch'` won't install a real fetch on top of the existing jest mock — the polyfill's IIFE checks `typeof self.fetch !== 'function'` and bails out when the mock is already there. So `installRealFetch()` must (a) remove the existing fetch, (b) bust the require-cache for `whatwg-fetch`, (c) re-require it, (d) verify a real (non-mock) fetch is installed.
